 g the simulation of large fluid volumes at cellular-scale resolution. To o
 vercome this challenge\, we introduce a new adaptive physics refinement (A
 PR) method that captures cellular-scale interaction across large domains a
 nd leverages a hybrid CPU-GPU approach to maximize performance. Through al
 gorithmic advances that integrate multi-physics and multi-resolution model
 s\, we establish a finely resolved window with explicitly modeled cells co
 upled to a coarsely resolved bulk fluid domain. In this work we present mu
